The cross product of two vectors $\begin{pmatrix} a \\ b \\ c \end{pmatrix}$ and $\begin{pmatrix} d \\ e \\ f \end{pmatrix}$ is given by
$$\begin{pmatrix} b f - c e \\ c d - a f \\ a e - b d \end{pmatrix}.$$So, the cross product of $\begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 0 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix}$ and $\begin{pmatrix} 5 \\ -1 \\ 7 \end{pmatrix}$ is
$$\begin{pmatrix} (0)(7) - (3)(-1) \\ (3)(5) - (2)(7) \\ (2)(-1) - (0)(5) \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 3 \\ 1 \\ -2 \end{pmatrix}.$$Thus, the cross product is $\boxed{\begin{pmatrix} 3 \\ 1 \\ -2 \end{pmatrix}}$.The answer is: \begin{pmatrix}3\1\-2\end{pmatrix}
